title: Swimmers find body at Coogee
text:
Share on Twitter 
A MAN’S body has been discovered on rocks at the northern end of Coogee Beach just metres from a surf life saving carnival. 
Swimmers discovered the body at the bottom of cliffs, near Giles Baths, and about 7am police were called. 
A crime scene has been established and the northern end of the beach roped off by police. 
The body was removed from the scene mid-morning. NSW Police are on the scene at Coogee. Picture: Julian Andrews   The body has since been taken away. picture: Julian Andrews   
The man is believed to have washed up on the rocks overnight, but the cause of his death is still unknown 
He was found without any identification or belongings and is believed to be in his 50s. 
Eastern Beaches Inspector Aaron Wunderlich said the man was yet to be identified, but his death did not appear to be suspicious. The body was discovered near Giles Baths. Source: Supplied A surf lifesaving carnival at the beach continued this morning after the discovery of the body. Picture: Julian Andrews   
“We are looking at all options, but at this stage there’s nothing to suggest it was suspicious,” he said. 
Inspector Wunderlich said a post mortem examination would likely determine the cause of the man’s death.
